, S Mgh.) See also each voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amarapN", "text_ar": "اَمَرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in three places. You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hiY A^amaArapu maA bayoniY wabayonaka", "text_ar": "هِى اَمَارَةُ مَا بَيْنِى وَبَيْنَكَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It is a sign,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "token, of what is between me and thee."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, * TA.) And a poet says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "A_i*aA TalaEato $amosu Aln~ahaAri faA_in~ahaA\n                      \n                      \n                        A^amaArapu tasoliymiY Ealayoki fasal~imiY"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "When the sun of day rises, it is a sign of my saluting thee, therefore do thou salute"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A time:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, K:) so IAar explains the latter word, not particularizing the time as definite or otherwise: (M:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a definite time:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a time,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "place, of promise"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "appointment; an appointed time"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "place;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mawoEidN", "text_ar": "مَوْعِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M, Mgh, K:) or, accord. to some, the former word is pl. [or rather col. gen. n.] of the latter. (TA.) El- 'Ajjáj says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "A_i*o rad~ahaA bikayodihi faArotad~ati\n                      \n                      \n                        A_ilay A^amaArK waA^amaAri mud~atiY"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "When He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(meaning God)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "brings it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(namely my soul,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by his skilful ordering,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and his power, ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and it is thus brought,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it thus comes, to a set time, and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the time of the end of my appointed period:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AmArmd~tY", "text_ar": "امارمدّتى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being as above; the former word being prefixed to the latter, governing it in the gen. case. (IB. [In the S we find"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waA^amaArN", "text_ar": "وَاَمَارٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mud~atiY", "text_ar": "مُدَّتِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".])"}], "source_refs": ["As", "S", "K", "M", "TA", "Mgh"]}, {"entry_id": "n1229", "headword_ar": "اَمَّارٌ", "root": "Amr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Wont to command"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~afosu AlA^am~aArapu", "text_ar": "النَّفْسُ الاَمَّارَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The soul that is wont to command"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (A;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the soul that inclines to the nature of the body, that commands to the indulgence of pleasures and sensual appetites, drawing the heart downwards, so that it is the abode of evils, and the source of culpable dispositions."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(KT.) [See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nafosN", "text_ar": "نَفْسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]"}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": {"source": "hawramani", "url": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A3%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1/", "headword_ar": "أَمَّار", "entries": [{"lexicon_id": "dictionary_48", "lexicon_en": "Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)", "lexicon_a